    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Migrations files and mainly `build` directory for the `development` network is a little annoying for a team working on a project, maybe migrations can be by default disabled and be activated by a configuration on `networks` config.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n    networks: {\r\n        development: {\r\n            host: '127.0.0.1',\r\n            port: 7545,\r\n            network_id: '*',\r\n            gasPrice: 1\r\n        },\r\n        mainnet: {\r\n            .\r\n            .\r\n            .\r\n            migrations: true\r\n        },\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
